The '''Foreign Languages Publishing House''' ({{Lang-ru|Издательство иностранной литературы}}) was a state-run publisher in the [[Soviet Union]] that published [[Russian language|Russian]] literature, novels, [[propaganda]], and books about the USSR in foreign languages.<ref name="Moscow : Foreign Languages Publishing House">{{cite web | url=http://toto.lib.unca.edu/findingaids/periodicals/foreign_language_moscow/foreign_languages_publishing_house.htm | title=Moscow : Foreign Languages Publishing House | publisher=University of North Carolina at Asheville | access-date=29 October 2013 | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080705171135/http://toto.lib.unca.edu/findingaids/periodicals/foreign_language_moscow/foreign_languages_publishing_house.htm | archivedate=5 July 2008 | df= }}</ref> These included works by [[Vladimir Lenin|Lenin]] and [[Joseph Stalin|Stalin]].<ref name="Moscow : Foreign Languages Publishing House"/> It was headquartered in [[Moscow]] at 21 Zubovsky Boulevard. It was founded in 1946, and in 1964 it was split into separate publishers [[Progress Publishers|Progress]] and [[Mir Publishers|Mir]].
==Book series published== * Classics of Russian Literature<ref>{{cite web|url=https://seriesofseries.owu.edu/classics-of-russian-literature/|title=Classics of Russian Literature|date=30 June 2017|website=seriesofseries.OWU.edu|access-date=3 February 2018}}</ref> * Library of Soviet Literature * Library of Selected Soviet Literature * Library of Marxist-Leninist Classics * Arts Library * Soviet Children's Library for Tiny Tots<ref>[http://www.publishinghistory.com/soviet-childrens-library-for-tiny-tots.html Soviet Children's Library for Tiny Tots (Foreign Languages Publishing House) - Book Series List], publishinghistory.com. Retrieved 21 May 2018.</ref> * Soviet Literature for Young People
