'''Hugh Lewin''' (born in 1939) is a South African anti-apartheid activist and writer. After a seven-year prison sentence, he left South Africa in 1971 and lived for ten years each in London and Zimbabwe.<ref name="jacana">{{cite web|url=http://www.jacana.co.za/our-authors-46564/2273-hugh-lewin|title=Hugh Lewin|work=Jacana Media|accessdate=4 November 2017}}</ref> He returned to South Africa in the 1990s.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.brandsouthafrica.com/south-africa-fast-facts/history-facts/bandiet|title=Hugh Lewin:|date=4 April 2003|accessdate=4 November 2017}}</ref> ''Bandiet: Out of Jail'' is illustrated by [[Harold Strachan]]. It won the 2003 [[Olive Schreiner Prize]], and ''Stones against the Mirror'' won the 2011 Sunday Times [[Alan Paton Award]].<ref name="jacana"/>

