'''Trophies of Damascus''' was a 7th-century [[Antisemitism|anti-Jewish]] tract written between 661 and 681 AD which presents an eye-witness accounts to the events that took place around that time period in the [[Middle East]]. It categorizes the nascent Saracens (Muslim) tribes as part of an alliance of Jewish clans fighting against the [[Byzantine]] [[Christians]] in contradiction to later accounts from traditional [[Islamic]] sources.

